 Kingsley English priest and author (b. 1819)\nBULLET::::- 1883 – Gustave Doré, French engraver and illustrator (b. 1832)\nBULLET::::- 1893 – Lucius Quintus Cincinnatus Lamar II, American lawyer and politician, 16th United States Secretary of the Interior (b. 1825)\nBULLET::::- 1893 – José Zorrilla, Spanish poet and playwright (b. 1817)\nBULLET::::- 1921 – Mykola Leontovych, Ukrainian composer and conductor (b. 1877)\nBULLET::::- 1922 – René Beeh, Alsatian painter and draughtsman (b. 1886)\nBULLET::::- 1922 – Arthur Nikisch, Hungarian conductor and academic (b. 1855)\nBULLET::::- 1923 – Max Nordau, Austrian physician and author (b. 1849)\nBULLET::::- 1931 – Anna Pavlova, Russian-English ballerina (b. 1881)\nBULLET::::- 1937 – Orso Mario Corbino, Italian physicist and politician (b. 1876)\nBULLET::::- 1939 – Matthias Sindelar, Austrian footballer and manager (b. 1903)\nBULLET::::- 1943 – Alexander Woollcott, American actor, playwright, and critic (b. 1887)\nBULLET::::- 1944 – Edvard Munch, Norwegian painter and illustrator (b. 1863)\nBULLET::::- 1947 – Pierre Bonnard, French painter (b. 1867)\nBULLET::::- 1956 – Alexander Korda, Hungarian-English director and producer (b. 1893)\nBULLET::::- 1963 – Józef Gosławski, Polish sculptor (b. 1908)\nBULLET::::- 1966 – T. M. Sabaratnam, Sri Lankan lawyer and politician (d. 1895)\nBULLET::::- 1971 – Fritz Feigl, Austrian-Brazilian chemist and academic (b. 1871)\nBULLET::::- 1973 – Alexander Onassis, American-Greek businessman (b. 1948)\nBULLET::::- 1973 – Kid Ory, American trombonist, composer, and bandleader (b. 1886)\nBULLET::::- 1976 – Paul Robeson, American actor, singer, and activist (b. 1898)\nBULLET::::- 1977 – Toots Shor, American businessman, founded Toots Shor's Restaurant (b. 1903)\nBULLET::::- 1978 – Terry Kath, American guitarist and songwriter (b. 1946)\nBULLET::::- 1978 – Jack Oakie, American actor (b. 1903)\nBULLET::::- 1980 – Giovanni Michelotti, Italian engineer (b. 1921)\nBULLET::::- 1981 – Samuel Barber, Ame