 and screenwriter (b. 1928)\nBULLET::::- 1986 – Raymond Loewy, French-American industrial designer (b. 1893)\nBULLET::::- 1989 – Frank Bell, English linguist and academic (b. 1916)\nBULLET::::- 1991 – Constance Stokes, Australian painter (b. 1906)\nBULLET::::- 1993 – Léo Ferré, Monacan singer-songwriter, pianist, and poet (b. 1916)\nBULLET::::- 1994 – César Tovar, Venezuelan baseball player (b. 1940)\nBULLET::::- 1996 – Jeff Krosnoff, American race car driver (b. 1964)\nBULLET::::- 1998 – Richard McDonald, American businessman, co-founded McDonald's (b. 1909)\nBULLET::::- 2000 – Pepo, Chilean cartoonist (b. 1911)\nBULLET::::- 2000 – William Roscoe Estep, American historian and academic (b. 1920)\nBULLET::::- 2000 – Meredith MacRae, American actress (b. 1944)\nBULLET::::- 2001 – Guy de Lussigny, French painter (b. 1929)\nBULLET::::- 2002 – Joaquín Balaguer, Dominican lawyer and politician, 41st President of the Dominican Republic (b. 1906)\nBULLET::::- 2002 – Fritz Glatz, Austrian race car driver (b. 1943)\nBULLET::::- 2003 – François-Albert Angers, Canadian economist and academic (b. 1909)\nBULLET::::- 2005 – Joe Harnell, American pianist and composer (b. 1924)\nBULLET::::- 2005 – Cicely Saunders, English hospice founder (b. 1918)\nBULLET::::- 2007 – John Ferguson Sr., Canadian ice hockey player, coach, and manager (b. 1938)\nBULLET::::- 2012 – John Arbuthnott, 16th Viscount of Arbuthnott, Scottish businessman and politician, Lord Lieutenant of Kincardineshire (b. 1924)\nBULLET::::- 2012 – Don Brinkley, American director, producer, and screenwriter (b. 1921)\nBULLET::::- 2012 – Frank R. Burns, American football player and coach (b. 1928)\nBULLET::::- 2012 – King Hill, American football player (b. 1936)\nBULLET::::- 2012 – Sixten Jernberg, Swedish skier (b. 1929)\nBULLET::::- 2012 – Roy Shaw, English businessman and boxer (b. 1936)\nBULLET::::- 2013 – Herbert M. Allison, American lieutenant and businessman (b. 1943)\nBULLET::::- 2013 – Matt Batts, American baseball p